## Conclusion

Per 第二十九章's own rule, one unmet condition is sufficient to withhold Level Five publication.
No row above reads NOT MET as of this update. Conditions 17, 18, 19 (generation-2 receipts as
the sole format, the v1->v2 migration itself receipted against this repo's own real history,
and replaying that real chain twice being deterministic) are now ALIVE, backed by real evidence
tied to this repo's actual production receipt log, not synthetic fixtures. Condition 8 (no
semantic contamination at composition time) gained a second real gate that closes the
term/individual-level cross-pack contamination gap this row previously named, alongside the
pre-existing path-collision gate -- but the row stays PARTIAL, not ALIVE, because that gate's
own coverage is narrower than the condition's full text (see condition 8's row above for the
precise scope: a closed 3-property functional-property list, and an rdf:type check with no
cross-pack provenance). Several rows remain honestly PARTIAL (this table's own Status column is
authoritative for the full list), each with a precisely named, narrower remaining gap -- e.g.
condition 5 (an independent, dissimilar-toolchain inspection path exists and was exercised, but
isn't wired into CI to run automatically) and condition 20 (same-host bit-identical
reproducibility is verified; a cross-host CI gate now exists in `release.yml` for one target
but has never actually run -- no tag has been pushed since it landed -- and covers only
`x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu` of the 4 real matrix targets). **ggen remains a
release candidate,
not a confirmed Level Five publication, until every PARTIAL row closes to ALIVE -- this pack
does not declare that threshold crossed by itself.** `RELEASE_STANDING.json`/`.md` record
`l5_publication_claim: WITHHELD` accordingly.
